That’s a catchy line with a nice internal rhyme.

A few variations depending on the tone you’re after:

* “Digital prophets. Converting insight into profit.” (professional)
* “Digital prophets. Turning patterns into profits.” (AI/data emphasis)
* “Digital prophets. We convert foresight into profits.” (business strategy)
* “Digital prophets don’t predict the future—they help build it. Then convert it into profits.” (longer tagline)
* “From digital prophets to digital profits.” (minimalist)
* “Digital prophets. Better questions. Better decisions. Better profits.” (less grandiose, more grounded)

If you’re thinking in terms of AI businesses, there’s a useful distinction: “prophets” works best as a metaphor for systems that synthesize information, spot emerging patterns, or help people reason about possibilities—not literally foretell the future. Framing it that way keeps the message both compelling and grounded.

It’s definitely a memorable hook that could work well for a presentation, a product, or even a short-form video.